          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            Chelsea played well. Defensively sound, Matic did his job, Fabregas and Hazard created a fair bit and Costa did his job with a nice finish. West Ham, however were very disappointing. If not for Adrian, it would've been a cricket score and they produced very little in attack. Granted they didn't have much of the ball and Chelsea closed down well, but West Ham surely would've expected to lose so why didn't they throw caution to the wind and attack more? A 2-0 loss is not much better in the grand scheme of things than a 5-0 one. Either that or park the bus but this was neither! The F.A also need to sort out the diving rule. Ivanovic for all intents and purposes dived but was slightly touched so officially it wasn't "simulation". A panel of ex-pros who know what is and isn't an attempt to cheat the ref with the power to retrospectively award cards (I, incidentally think a dive should warrant a straight red) would stamp diving out of the game fairly quickly.
